    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Plain knit fabric formed with knit and purl sides, usually referring to fine machine-knitted fabric generally. This type of knit was originally a staple industry of the British isle of Jersey.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
